<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,802,970]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,802,827]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body oval and shinning. Head vertical, triangular, strongly transverse, obtusely round between antennae; clypeus vertical, compressed and strongly projecting at base of the antennae; front flat and smooth; eyes small, with posterior margin straight; antennal segment I slender on basal 
<number box="[905,916,874,898]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[927,942,874,898]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="3.0">3</number>
, thicker than the other segments, and nearly reaching the apex of the clypeus; rostrum usually very thick, short, reaching the anterior coxae. Pronotum with large collarlike anterior margin; calli long and oblique, somewhat convex; disc smooth or slightly punctate.
</paragraph>
